definitions.definition: ( intransitive ) To touch by means of a mutual border , edge or end ; to border on; to lie adjacent (to); to be contiguous (said of an area of land) [First attested around 1350 to 1470.]
examples: It was a time when Germany still abutted upon Russia.
His land abuts on the road.

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To border upon; be next to; abut on ; be adjacent to. [First attested in the mid-19 century.]

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To touch by means of a mutual border , edge or end ; to border on; to lie adjacent (to); to be contiguous (said of an area of land) [First attested around 1350 to 1470.]

definitions.definition: To lean against on one end; to end on, of a part of a building or wall.
definitions.dating_raw: First attested in the late 16 century.
